Male genitalia. Median lobe broad, slightly conical and curved ventrally towards apex with deep incision (
Fig. 55
). Tectum nearly as large as half of median lobe consisting of two long, broad, tectorial spurs ventrally curved at apex. In lateral view these spurs are dilated in upper half just before turning down into distinct hook towards apex. Endophallus, divisable in two parts, apical part with endophallic brush and simple basal part, which is less than double the length of apical part.
